.TH MONITOR_THING 1 "2025-11-02" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
monitor_thing \- system monitoring utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B monitor_thing
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B monitor_thing
is a system monitoring utility that displays system usage statistics in real-time.
The utility continuously polls system metrics and displays them in a formatted table.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-poll\-rate " " \fIRATE\fR
Set the polling rate in miliseconds (default: 500).
Valid range is 10 to 36000 miliseconds.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Monitor system with default 500 milisecond polling:
.B monitor_thing
.TP
Monitor system with 5000 second polling interval:
.B monitor_thing \-p 5
.TP
Display help information:
.B monitor_thing \-\-help
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful program execution or help displayed.
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred (invalid arguments, out of range values, etc.).
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGINT
Gracefully shut down the monitoring loop and exit.
